  "riddle": "1. Seek the gaming powerhouse based in a city often referred to as the Big Apple. Which bustling capital of commerce lends its name to this publisher?\n\n2. What is the height above sea level for this urban marvel where dreams and skyscrapers touch the sky?\n\n3. Nearby this vibrant hub, how many places of worship can be found nestled in its cultural tapestry?\n\n4. Combine the elevation you discovered in clue 2 with the church count from clue 3; what is their absolute difference?\n\n5. Turn your attention to a beloved franchise where a young hero traverses worlds, releasing its first installment in what year?\n\n6. This streaming service, born in 2020, proudly showcases tales and dramas. Since which month and year has its emblem graced the digital screens of its viewers?\n\n7. Among the valiant bookshelves, how many repositories of knowledge dot the landscape surrounding both a lively metropolis and its neighboring borough?\n\n8. In the metropolis known for its towering monuments and vibrant culture, what is noted as the highest point within its expanse?\n\n9. How much higher does the ground rise in this concrete jungle, when considering its elevation again?\n\n10. Look around this urban center: how many venues dedicated to art and history can be found among its streets?\n\n11. Now, merge the elevation from clue 9 with the muse count from clue 10—what is the absolute difference you uncover?\n\n12. In a city steeped in history, what is the altitude found where ancient marvels unfold in this notable land?\n\n13. Take the elevation value unearthed in clue 12 and distill it down to its digital essence—what singular figure emerges?\n\n14. The much-anticipated exhibition in the heart of Europe takes place every March; calculate how many days stretch from the start of a new year in 2025 to this celebratory event in 2026.\n\n15. Extract the essence of the number of days from clue 14 by summing its digits—what total do you reach?\n\n16. Finally, compute the expression: take the sum of the results from clues 7, 9, and 12, then apply modulo 10 to it. What single digit do you arrive at?",
